{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly to the Social model, we estimate these two additional models on the four survey questions separately, applying a logarithmic transformation to the nEMD distances to better match their observed approximate log-normal distribution.",
    "We first look at the goodness of fit of the three models.",
    "Table 5 presents two measures for each of these linear models, adjusted R 2 and the Bayesian Information Criterion (BIC).",
    "Under the machine bias hypothesis, we expect the R 2 of the Center model to be higher than that of the Social model, and to be generally very high, and the BIC to be symmetrically lower.",
    "Both measures account for the difference in model sizes (24 predictors for the Social model, 1 for the Center model, 25 for the Full model); the BIC is known to give a stronger penalty to models with more predictors."
  ]
}